==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pollution
<hw>Pol*lu"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pollutio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pollution</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of polluting, or the state of being polluted (in any sense
of the verb); defilement; uncleanness; impurity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The emission of semen, or sperm,
at other times than in sexual intercourse.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pollux</ent>⟦br⟧
